parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt buckle can lead to the inability to properly restrain occupants, increasing the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt buckle fails to latch
the seat belt will not lock
the seat belt retractor does not retract
the seat belt release button does not properly fasten.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure to properly repair recalled seat belt buckles can lead to continued safety risks for occupants, increasing the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: Recall repairs not performed due to lack of parts
seat belt buckle failure after recall repairs.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Environmental Factors Affecting Seat Belt Buckles
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The degradation of seat belt buckle materials due to environmental factors, such as sun exposure, can lead to the failure of the seat belt buckle, increasing the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: Plastic degradation in rear and center seat belt buckles due to sun exposure.
